# vofy-cli — Media Generation

vofy-cli is a CLI for the Vofy media generation platform (21 models, image + video).

Before using it, make sure the user has installed `vofy-cli` with `npm install -g vofy-cli@0.1.3` and authenticated with `vofy login`.

## Rules for AI Agents

- Always use `--yes` on create commands (skips interactive route picker)
- Always use `--plain` on `vofy tasks` (avoids the interactive task browser in TTY sessions)
- Use `--download-to <path>` when you need local files; otherwise the default sync output already shows result URLs
- Never run `vofy login` — requires browser, tell user to do it manually

## Quick Reference

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `vofy status` | Check auth and credits |
| `vofy image create` | Create image |
| `vofy video create` | Create video |
| `vofy task <id_or_prefix>` | Task detail / URLs / download |
| `vofy tasks --plain` | List tasks |
| `vofy models` | List models |
| `vofy billing` | Open pricing or switch plans |

## Image Creation

```bash
vofy image create --model seedream-4.5 --prompt "<prompt>" --yes --download-to ./output
```

Modes: text_to_image (default), image_to_image (`--image <path>`), inpainting (`--image <path> --mask <path>`)

Top models: `seedream-4.5` (general, 4K), `gpt-image-1.5` (transparent bg, inpainting), `seedream-5.0-lite` (web search)

## Video Creation

```bash
vofy video create --model veo-3.1 --prompt "<prompt>" --duration 6 --yes --download-to ./output
```

Modes: text_to_video, image_to_video (`--first-frame`), interpolation (`--first-frame` + `--last-frame`), reference_images (`--reference-image`), multimodal_reference (`--mode multimodal_reference --reference-image ... --reference-video ...`), video_to_video (`--mode video_to_video --video`), video_extension (`--mode video_extension --video`), motion_control

Top models: `veo-3.1` (4K, best quality), `kling-3.0` (15s, audio, multi-shot), `seedance-2.0` (most versatile, 7 modes)

Task tips: `vofy tasks` opens an interactive browser in a TTY unless you pass `--plain`; `vofy task` accepts a unique task id prefix; `vofy task <id_or_prefix> --result-url` prints generated resource URLs.

Billing tips: `vofy billing` opens an interactive picker in a TTY; `vofy billing starter|pro|max` or `vofy billing --plan <plan>` skips the picker.

## Error Handling

- Not authenticated → tell user to run `vofy login`
- Insufficient credits → tell user to check `vofy billing`
- Model not found → run `vofy models`
- Invalid parameter → check `vofy models <name>`
